INSERT INTO bytes.bytes (id, author_id, title, body, code_snippet, language, embedding, type, is_active, created_at, updated_at) VALUES (
  '167e1378-afee-4bb6-b9fc-9f3c0552a93e',
  '00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001',
  $escape$Prometheus Exemplars — Correlation IDs That Bridge Metrics and Logs$escape$,
  $escape$Prometheus doesn't manage logs natively — but exemplars make it the correlation layer between them. Enable exemplar storage with `--enable-feature=exemplar-storage`, then attach a `trace_id` label to histogram/summary observations using `ObserveWithExemplar()`. When a latency spike appears in Grafana, you jump directly from the metric data point to the matching trace or Loki log entry — no manual time-window hunting.

For Prometheus's own runtime logs, two flags matter: `--log.format=json` emits structured output consumable by any log aggregator, and `--log.level=warn` keeps production noise minimal while surfacing actionable scrape failures and TSDB errors.

Know the retention gotcha: exemplar storage is a fixed ring buffer, controlled by `--storage.exemplars.exemplars-limit` (default 100,000 entries). Unlike TSDB blocks where `--storage.tsdb.retention.time` bounds by age, exemplars flush by count. A high-traffic endpoint with 50 label combinations can evict exemplars within minutes. Keep exemplar label sets lean — one `trace_id` per observation, aligned with the OpenTelemetry exemplar spec.

Query exemplars directly: `GET /api/v1/query_exemplars?query=http_request_duration_seconds&start=<unix>&end=<unix>`.$escape$,
  $escape$import (
    "github.com/prometheus/client_golang/prometheus"
    "github.com/prometheus/client_golang/prometheus/promauto"
)

var requestDuration = promauto.NewHistogramVec(prometheus.HistogramOpts{
    Name:    "http_request_duration_seconds",
    Buckets: prometheus.DefBuckets,
}, []string{"method", "status"})

// ObserveWithExemplar attaches a trace_id correlation ID to the metric sample.
func recordRequest(method, status, traceID string, duration float64) {
    requestDuration.WithLabelValues(method, status).(prometheus.ExemplarObserver).
        ObserveWithExemplar(duration, prometheus.Labels{"trace_id": traceID})
}$escape$,
  $escape$go$escape$,
