INSERT INTO bytes.bytes (id, author_id, title, body, code_snippet, language, embedding, type, is_active, created_at, updated_at) VALUES (
  'cf5500f8-6b57-4771-8227-a76a47dd578f',
  '00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001',
  $escape$Prometheus Alertmanager — Escalation Policies, Inhibition, and Postmortem Timelines$escape$,
  $escape$When an incident fires, your Alertmanager routing tree is your first line of triage. Structure routes so `warning` alerts fan out to Slack and `critical` alerts page on-call via PagerDuty — set `continue: false` to stop at the first match and prevent duplicate pages.

Inhibition rules suppress alert storms during cascades. An `inhibit_rule` matching on `job` and `instance` labels silences all `warning` alerts when a `critical` is already active on the same target, keeping on-call focused on the root cause rather than its symptoms.

For postmortems, `ALERTS_FOR_STATE{alertname="HighErrorRate"}` returns the Unix timestamp each alert entered `pending`, letting you reconstruct exact timelines in Grafana without scrubbing Slack history. Pair with `changes(ALERTS_FOR_STATE[1h])` to surface flapping events.

Always monitor Alertmanager itself: `alertmanager_notifications_failed_total` by `integration` exposes silent delivery failures to PagerDuty or Slack that would otherwise go undetected. A dead man's switch — a recording rule that always evaluates true and must continuously fire — validates your full alerting pipeline end-to-end.

During maintenance windows, create targeted silences via `amtool` without touching alert rule files.$escape$,
  $escape$# Reconstruct incident timeline — when did alert enter pending state?
# Returns Unix timestamp per label set
ALERTS_FOR_STATE{alertname="HighErrorRate", job="payment-api"}

# Count flap events over the incident window
changes(ALERTS_FOR_STATE{alertname="HighErrorRate"}[1h])

# Detect silent Alertmanager delivery failures post-incident
alertsmanager_notifications_failed_total{integration="pagerduty"}

# Create a scoped silence during postmortem maintenance (no rule edits)
amtool silence add \
  -l alertname=HighErrorRate \
  -l job=payment-api \
  --duration=2h \
  --comment="Postmortem: validating fix before re-enabling"$escape$,
  $escape$bash$escape$,
